<section class="hero">

<h1>
Meta<span>bolomics</span>
</h1>

<p>
Metabolomics investigates the small molecules and metabolites that reflect real-time biochemical activity within biological systems. By measuring metabolic pathways, cellular energy states, and disease-associated chemical signatures, metabolomics connects molecular regulation to phenotype, physiology, and human health.
</p>

<div class="hero-image">
  <video autoplay muted loop playsinline>
    <source src="/3_Metabolomics.mp4" type="video/mp4">
  </video>
</div>

</section>

<section class="section">

<h2>
What is <span>Metabolomics?</span>
</h2>

<div class="infographic">

  <img
    src="/1_Metabolomics.png"
    alt="Metabolomics overview infographic"
  >

</div>

<p>
Metabolomics is the study of small molecules, metabolites, and biochemical pathways that reflect the real-time physiological state of cells, tissues, organisms, and environments.
</p>

<p>
Modern metabolomics uses mass spectrometry, nuclear magnetic resonance, pathway analysis, and computational biology to understand metabolism, disease mechanisms, biomarkers, drug response, and precision health.
</p>

