<section class="section">

<h2>
Metabolomics and <span>Omics Sciences</span>
</h2>

<p>
Metabolomics provides a direct snapshot of biochemical activity by measuring the metabolites produced through cellular processes. It captures the functional outcome of genomic, transcriptomic, proteomic, environmental, and physiological influences.
</p>

<p>
At PanorOmics, metabolomics serves as a critical layer for understanding cellular metabolism, disease mechanisms, biomarker discovery, precision health, and systems-level biology.
</p>

